          "2c_score": 3,
          "2c_reason": "Transitions are sometimes plausible (mirrored Scooby Doo/Points; Which-a-way into Points; Wrist roll into Lock), but there are multiple potentially abrupt or physically tight links: jump into wide stance then drag with slow wrist roll (29-31) may conflict with groove continuity; “double Up lock (43) then drop low Which-a-way (44)” is sharp but may need an intermediate sink; “Jump Lock” with a “suspended aerial freeze” is questionable at 115 BPM and may break locking aesthetics/landings without setup.",
          "3a_score": 4,
